<subSubSection id="7B5B90F9A9348ED7F9711CBB48A4C879" lastPageId="805" lastPageNumber="806" pageId="804" pageNumber="805" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="953EFFF318A3E2B2500BF07F8C0AAB71" lastPageId="805" lastPageNumber="806" pageId="804" pageNumber="805">
<taxonomicName id="96056CB898BC5FC799F1183A93D44799" authorityName="Hope" authorityYear="1838" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Philorhizus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="804" pageNumber="805" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Philorhizus</taxonomicName>
Hope, 1838: 63. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="C75527A9DB3D5655188D81D4E854F5E6" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Carabus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="804" pageNumber="805" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciatus">
<emphasis id="562B20D263A712E87CD813D8FCC98E31" italics="true" pageId="804" pageNumber="805">Carabus fasciatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Paykull, 1790 (= 
<taxonomicName id="08B9F4ED2047171F3E4FFEE1D7874764" authorityName="P. Rossi" authorityYear="1790" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Carabus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="804" pageNumber="805" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sigma">
<emphasis id="9B334F988E41567844612F43CEC09665" italics="true" pageId="804" pageNumber="805">Carabus sigma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Rossi, 1790) by original designation. Etymology (original). Anagram of the 
<pageBreakToken id="7CAA45CC97AC2851360EFCBDED2789C3" pageId="805" pageNumber="806" start="start">generic</pageBreakToken>
name 
<taxonomicName id="C7C5933615D1F825E669AB68DE59F6D8" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Risophilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="805" pageNumber="806" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="EE94C549FB0343278E3F3F824C065ECE" italics="true" pageId="805" pageNumber="806">Risophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as 
<taxonomicName id="06D02F2B9611111A5CFF8FD770E4603F" genus="Rizophilus" lsidName="" pageId="805" pageNumber="806" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C5D66584B2897207007D4659512B4D9E" italics="true" pageId="805" pageNumber="806">Rizophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), derived from the Greek 
<emphasis id="790F27F20F574C66F9243AA605F7A5AC" italics="true" pageId="805" pageNumber="806">philos</emphasis>
(beloved) and 
<emphasis id="3D61479BFBACD75BF27BB94B1C8CD7E4" italics="true" pageId="805" pageNumber="806">rhiza</emphasis>
(root) [masculine].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="26074E3AB6F083D0F3E949E15C61E95B" pageId="805" pageNumber="806">
<taxonomicName id="619722CC8CD0B96D381190E2D824375F" authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1905" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Dromiolus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="805" pageNumber="806" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Dromiolus</taxonomicName>
Reitter, 1905: 230, 235. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="DB5928C79F4C7263C121E7BF6553625F" authorityName="C. G. Thomson" authorityYear="1857" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dromius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="805" pageNumber="806" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriventris">
<emphasis id="8CE0A848E696A4DD9D815DC68606A75E" italics="true" pageId="805" pageNumber="806">Dromius nigriventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Thomson, 1857 (= 
<taxonomicName id="929A698415E379E5E8261923533D4030" authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1827" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dromius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="805" pageNumber="806" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="notatus">
<emphasis id="C1B41D7A9E3500AA53CFABD22F3E4F0F" italics="true" pageId="805" pageNumber="806">Dromius notatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Stephens, 1827) by original designation. Etymology. From the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="559E34B91F4BBF02E7E82578390B594E" authorityName="Bonelli" authorityYear="1810" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dromius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="805" pageNumber="806" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C9BA14FF8C642AA845D06337E9970A5B" italics="true" pageId="805" pageNumber="806">Dromius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[
<emphasis id="0CF4F2674C99C7C0AC4DFE4666AE2A44" italics="true" pageId="805" pageNumber="806">q.v</emphasis>
.] and the Latin suffix - 
<emphasis id="A049986DE7C70AE6E1EBEB57E95D460F" italics="true" pageId="805" pageNumber="806">olus</emphasis>
(diminutive) [masculine].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C5571B6BC872ABC9D454FC466474F2F0" pageId="805" pageNumber="806">
<taxonomicName id="0D6BDB352E6BA852AB30E3779F995B63" authorityName="Mateu" authorityYear="1953" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Similidromius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="805" pageNumber="806" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Similidromius</taxonomicName>
Mateu, 1953: 140. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="FB18472AEF002CF8782B049B682842A2" authorityName="Wollaston" authorityYear="1864" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dromius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="805" pageNumber="806" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elliptipennis">
<emphasis id="D4813BE5CD2D8252F47008C66BD0D458" italics="true" pageId="805" pageNumber="806">Dromius elliptipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Wollaston, 1864 by monotypy. Synonymy established by Machado (1992: 519). Etymology. From the Latin adjective 
<emphasis id="A8EBBD04263F7FC405A9D560C2AD5C7B" italics="true" pageId="805" pageNumber="806">similis</emphasis>
, - 
<emphasis id="2AFBDA919191819EC104B46E448A6975" italics="true" pageId="805" pageNumber="806">e</emphasis>
(like) and the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="67B4B33750988620F720EA54CC5C76D0" authorityName="Bonelli" authorityYear="1810" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dromius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="805" pageNumber="806" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1BA6A4A5CE0FD7D119482AF032617036" italics="true" pageId="805" pageNumber="806">Dromius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[
<emphasis id="6F9651F405D9F63CE45BF740838197A1" italics="true" pageId="805" pageNumber="806">q.v</emphasis>
.], alluding to the resemblance of the species in the hands of Mateu to those of 
<taxonomicName id="DB34CC2E65AEB6F579FE5C27D0156B0D" authorityName="Bonelli" authorityYear="1810" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Dromius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="805" pageNumber="806" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="78394981C6CDEE3DE4E4E9304C3631FC" italics="true" pageId="805" pageNumber="806">Dromius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[masculine].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EA34D030D5A2343CD0C7351DA37388BE" pageId="805" pageNumber="806" type="diversity">
<paragraph id="45D798A235A01A876D7005190D356D8B" pageId="805" pageNumber="806">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7C734DDB5557BE68BC9EAA1961E0A189" pageId="805" pageNumber="806">About 50 species (Lorenz 2005: 477) in the Nearctic (two species, one of them adventive), Oriental (two species), Palaearctic (about 35 species, 15 of them endemic to the Canary and Madeira Islands), and Afrotropical (11 species) Regions.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="21764CE5A10C33D9D4DF48356D00E20F" pageId="805" pageNumber="806" type="identification">
<paragraph id="324A451A3FBD945A5A32D8ABE64526C9" pageId="805" pageNumber="806">Identification.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="89FD523795094C4BE602D7BB7A016821" pageId="805" pageNumber="806">Bousquet (2004b: 49-51) commented on the structural differences between the two species found in North America.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
